    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "`col('v')` does not return the correct value after hitting `viw` from the end of a `<cword>`,\nbut it does when hitting `ve` or `vb`, or `viw` (from anywhere except the end of a `<cword>`).\n\nAs soon as you hit `v_o`, `col('v')` becomes correct.\n\nSeems like the state behind \"v\" is not updated soon enough or falls in some edge case?\n\nNote: The problem also happens when using `getpos` instead of `col`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nconf.lua\n```lua\nfunction DebugVisualSelection()\n    return string.format(\"v %s  . %s  \", vim.fn.col(\"v\"), vim.fn.col(\".\"))\nend\n\nvim.o.statusline = \"%!v:lua.DebugVisualSelection()\"\n```\n\n```sh\necho \"abc\" > demo\nnvim --clean -u conf.lua demo\n```\n\n| position | action | statusline | result |\n| -------- | ------ | ---------- |:------:|\n| `a`      | `ve`   | `v 1  . 3` | ✅     |\n| `a`      | `viw`  | `v 1  . 3` | ✅     |\n| `b`      | `viw`  | `v 1  . 3` | ✅     |\n| `c`      | `vb`   | `v 3  . 1` | ✅     |\n| `c`      | `viw`  | `v 3  . 3` | ❌     |\n\n---\n\nDoes not occur with vim (9.0):\n\n```vim\nfunction! DebugVisualSelection()\n    return printf(\"v %s  . %s\", col(\"v\"), col(\".\"))\nendfunction\n\nset laststatus=2\nset statusline=%!DebugVisualSelection()\n```\n\n```sh\necho \"abc\" > demo\nnvim --clean -u conf.lua demo\n```\n\n| position | action | statusline | result |\n| -------- | ------ | ---------- |:------:|\n| `a`      | `ve`   | `v 1  . 3` | ✅     |\n| `a`      | `viw`  | `v 1  . 3` | ✅     |\n| `b`      | `viw`  | `v 1  . 3` | ✅     |\n| `c`      | `vb`   | `v 3  . 1` | ✅     |\n| `c`      | `viw`  | `v 1  . 3` | ✅     |\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`col('v')` should return the leftmost column position after hitting `viw`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0 commit a99c469e54\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11 Pro 10.0.26100 Build 26100, WSL 2.6.1.0\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal 1.23.12811\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from source",
